This directory may contain developer utility scripts.

The MyGenMOOSApp script is similar to that found in the moos-ivp/trunk/scripts/
directory. Users are encouraged to tailor this one to their own needs.

Current repo-specific helpers:

- `ci_harness_case_count.py` derives the default case count from a harness
  `zlaunch.sh` so GitHub Actions can reject incomplete `results.txt` files.
- `ci_cpp_test_targets.py` builds the C++ unit test target matrix, runs CTest
  label targets, writes per-target JUnit XML reports, and appends a C++ unit
  test summary to GitHub Actions.
- `harness_targets.py` validates and selects the manual-dispatch harness
  target metadata in `config/harness_targets.json`.
- `check_repo_invariants.py` checks that harness target metadata, docs catalog
  entries, workflow dispatch choices, default case lists, and generated docs
  stay in sync.
- `list_harness_targets.py` prints the configured manual-dispatch families and
  targets for quick local inspection.
- `benchmark_parallel.sh` runs repeatable wall-clock timing sweeps for a
  harness across multiple `--jobs` values and writes the summary under
  `time_benchmarking/`.
- `repeatability_sweep.py` reruns one harness multiple times at a fixed
  configuration, saves raw logs/results, and writes a per-case stability
  summary under `time_benchmarking/`.
- `moos_ivp_build_matrix.py` validates and selects standalone MOOS-IvP build
  portability targets and build-profile compatibility from
  `config/moos_ivp_build_targets.json`.
- `build_moos_ivp_target.sh` installs build dependencies for the current
  Linux target, clones a selected MOOS-IvP ref, and runs either the full or
  headless MOOS-IvP build without invoking this repo's tests or missions.
